Ok, I've heard several arguments over how to properly warm up your bus when
starting it cold....  So what is the correct way?  I would assume if I had a
stock setup with heat risers it would be different or faster than my current
setup with a bugpack header and dual carbs.  I park on a hill when not in
hte garage and currently use the start the engine with a few pumps of gas
and continue out of the driveway.  Others recommend warming the engine prior
to driving away.  I recently read in the Muir book to not warm it in the
driveway....


